HEADWORD: Macowanites americanus
<hw>Macowanites americanus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A
small fungus with a fragile cap that cracks to expose the white context
and a white stalk that is practically enclosed by the cap.</def>⟦br⟧
